criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  1. healthy children

  2. with Asymptomatic primary molars with a deep carious lesion;

  3. Exposure of a vital pulp by caries;

  4. No clinical or radiographic evidence of pulp degeneration, such as excessive bleeding
     from the root canal, internal root resorption, inter-radicular and/or periapical bone
     destruction,swelling, or sinus tract;

  5. Ability to perform a leakage free restoration of the teeth using stainless steel
     crown, or amalgam/resin based restoration.
